Rating: 3
This was a delicious salad with the mix of potatoes. I think 35 minutes is too long on the grill; in addition, I made the mistake of letting my foil cool before unwrapping the potatoes, so mine were a bit too soft. But still great for a warm weather supper. I used 1/4 C. light olive oil mayo and 1/4 C. plain yogurt to lighten it up. Everyone loved it!

Rating: 1
I was really dissappointed in this potato salad. Apparently so was everyone else at the BBQ where I took it as hardly anyone ate it. It tastes very much like a German potato salad. If you like that type - I suppose it's ok. One change I would recommend is to grill the sweet potatoes less than 35 minutes as mine got a bit too mushy. I would go with 25 minutes.

Rating: 4
What a hit - we had a pre-4th BBQ party yesterday. In my hast to prepare everything I did not follow the directions and cut all the potatoes up into 1" pieces and put them in the foil packets. We did not reduce the grilling time and of course they burned. I decided to prepare the salad anyway and see if it was any good. People RAVED about the salad. I can't wait to make it again and NOT burn the potatoes.

