I made this with barbequed ribs and it was delicious. I will make it again. It is very flavorful and everyone liked it as much as I did. Thanks for the recipe, Epicurious.

Rating: 4
This was an amazing salad! I have made it 3 times in two weeks. The lemon is the key along with less mayo than many traditional potato salads. This is really a fresh and different salad; you can be proud to bring it along to all your that summer BBQ's! I used red potatoes because purples can be hard to find this time of year. DO NOT OMIT the sweet potatoes either - they add so much interest!

Rating: 4
I made a lightened version of the recipe, using 1/4 c. lemon juice, 2 T. Dijon, and 3 T. olive oil. Plus, I roasted the potatoes in the oven rather than grilling them. It was absolutely fantastic. I served it slightly warm as a side dish with grilled salmon and asparagus. Guests raved about the meal and the salad in particular.

